wed": Resistance and Worship at the Anchor Fellowship -- t10 Hillsong Abroad: Tracing the Songlines of Contemporary Pentecostal Music -- tPart III Media, Culture, and the Marketplace -- t11 Charismatic Music and the Pentecostalization of Latin American Evangelicalism -- t12 Blessed to Be a Blessing: The Prosperity Gospel of Worship Music Superstar Israel Houghton -- t13 Music, Culture Industry, and the Shaping of Charismatic Worship: An Autobiographical/Conversational Engagement -- t14 We Can't Go Back: Liturgies of Worship and Consumer Culture at One African American Church -- t15 Gospel Funk: Pentecostalism, Music, and Popular Culture in Rio de Janeiro -- tConclusion Improvisation, Indigenization, and Inspiration: Theological Reflections on the Sound and Spirit of Global Renewal -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn The Spirit of Praise, Monique Ingalls and Amos Yong bring together a multidisciplinary, scholarly exploration of music and worship in global pentecostal-charismatic Christianity at the beginning of the twenty-first century. The Spirit of Praise contends that gaining a full understanding of this influential religious movement requires close listening to its songs and careful attention to its patterns of worship. The essays in this volume place ethnomusicological, theological, historical, and sociological perspectives into dialogue. By engaging with these disciplines and exploring themes of interconnection, interface, and identity within musical and ritual practices, the essays illuminate larger social processes such as globalization, sacralization, and secularization, as well as the role of religion in social and cultural change. Aside from the editors, the contributors are Peter Althouse, Will Boone, Mark Evans, Ryan R. Gladwin, Birgitta J. Johnson, Jean Ngoya Kidula, Miranda Klaver, Andrew Mall, Kimberly Jenkins Marshall, Andrew M. McCoy, Martijn Oosterbaan, Dave Perkins, Wen Reagan, Tanya Riches, Michael Webb, and Michael Wilkinson.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aMusicxReligious aspectsxPentecostal churches. 0aPentecostal churches. 0aWorship. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Pentecostal & Charismatic.2bisacsh1 aAlthouse, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoone, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGladwin, Ryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngalls, Monique M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIngalls, Monique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Birgitta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKidula, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlaver, Miranda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMall, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarshall, Kimberly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCoy, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOosterbaan, Martijn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerkins, Dave, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReagan, Wen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiches, Tanya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWebb, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilkinson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYong, Amos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.